x4freetext: Extraction of (m,Ek) for primary fragments
242Pu (enriched to 99.74%, 25 mm diam. active layer):
90 ug/cm2 PuF3 layer on a 30 ug/cm2 polyimide backing
with 10 ug/cm2 Au prepared by evaporation.
242Pu(sf) measurements were done during shut-down
periods of the linac for 242Pu(g,f) measurements.
Two Ortec F-series heavy ion detectors (CF-35-
600-60) mounted symmetrically on both sides of the
fission target at 90 deg and at a distance of
7 cm to the beam axis.
Based on mass and momentum conservation relations and
the detector calibration procedure, the pulse heights
of the coincident fission fragments were converted
off line in two-dimensional provisional mass and
kinetic energy arrays of 120x120 channels.
Two-dimensional preneutron mass and total kinetic
energy arrays were deduced by using an iterative
procedure described by Schmitt
On+LV
at Ee=12 and 18 MeV
